"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-tom-daley-paris-olympics-2024-noah-williams-b2540659.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Daley announced a retirement U-turn last year to target more glory in Paris this summer after winning gold in Tokyo in the 10-metre synchro event, with diving partner Noah Williams confident they can shine  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 528, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 286, \"end\": 291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999977617335, \"rank\": 2.2381433116631065e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 326, \"end\": 331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7829467599616518, \"rank\": 0.27722605076130374, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 383, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\", \"score\": 0.999998273608197, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Noah Williamsinsists diving partnerTom Daleyis in a class of his own after bouncing back from the brink of retirement to reach a fifth Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 29-year-old has been named amongTeam GB's first eight divers for Paris this summer just a year after announcing a retirement U-turn.\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 745, \"end\": 747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9961371706345673, \"rank\": 0.0038774267458044805, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 773, \"end\": 778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999977617335, \"rank\": 2.2381433116631065e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daley said he wasinspired by son Robbieto go full pelt forParis 2024, despite not competing in the two years since he finally won Olympic gold in the 10-metre synchro event with now-injured Matty Lee in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 1051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1032, \"end\": 1041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matty_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matty Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matty_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matty_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 1045, \"end\": 1050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7829467599616518, \"rank\": 0.27722605076130374, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he will team up with new partner Williams to defend his title - and the pair are among the medal favourites.\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They qualified for the Games with silver at the World Championships in Doha earlier in the year, and are one of four formidable pairs that will represent Team GB at the Olympic Aquatics Centre.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1238, \"end\": 1242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"score\": 0.9999999999849933, \"rank\": 1.4863113733658588e-11, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\"}, {\"begin\": 1321, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9995808415400871, \"rank\": 0.00041933422722299714, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Williams, who is set for his second Olympics after competing in the individual 10m event in Tokyo, said: \\\"I do not think people realise how good Tom is.\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1514, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7829467599616518, \"rank\": 0.27722605076130374, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is no one else in the world who could have two years out and then come back and be a world medallist and world champion in the team event.\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1661, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's insanely hard-working and talented, he's miles above everyone else.\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Anything can happen on the day, we have done really well this year and I hope I can help Tom out.\\\"\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1837, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB have confirmed the first eight divers in the team, while the British Diving Championships in May will play a key role in deciding the rest, with individual spots still up for grabs.\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 2028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9995808415400871, \"rank\": 0.00041933422722299714, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1908, \"end\": 1915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.8113459744317659, \"rank\": 0.14387833553168392, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 1916, \"end\": 1922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diving_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0257632886829895e-14, \"text\": \"Diving\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diving_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diving_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daley is not the only Olympic champion on the roster.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2083, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rio 2016 3m synchronised springboard champion Jack Laugher is another taking the plunge at his fourth Games.\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2130, \"end\": 2142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Laugher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jack Laugher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Laugher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Laugher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 29-year-old battled with his mental health following gold eight years ago but reignited his diving fire with a hard-fought individual 3m springboard bronze in Japan.\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2357, \"end\": 2362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9568553210355194, \"rank\": 0.035997293327115314, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He partners diving debutant Anthony Harding, who Laugher admits has further lit his desire to give a fourth Games his all.\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2393, \"end\": 2408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Harding_(archaeologist)\", \"score\": 0.8333269169617231, \"rank\": 0.19999999999996818, \"text\": \"Anthony Harding\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Harding_(archaeologist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Harding_(archaeologist)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Laugher said: \\\"I never thought when I was a kid I would ever make it to one, let alone four so I am extremely proud.\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's ignited that spark in me that I needed as I am getting older and, as athletes do age, it's important to keep that fire burning.\", \"from\": 2607, \"to\": 2740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's exciting taking Anthony into his first Olympic Games as well so I am really looking forward to it and hoping it's as good as it can be.\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2883, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Before Tokyo is a difficult time to speak about but it's a fond Games to look back on and to know how strong I can be.\\\"\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 3005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2893, \"end\": 2898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7829467599616518, \"rank\": 0.27722605076130374, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB have also picked arguably their best ever female synchro squad, including Andrea Spendolini-Sirieix and Lois Toulson in the 10m synchro.\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3007, \"end\": 3014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9995808415400871, \"rank\": 0.00041933422722299714, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3089, \"end\": 3114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrea_Spendolini-Sirieix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andrea Spendolini-Sirieix\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrea_Spendolini-Sirieix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrea_Spendolini-Sirieix\"}, {\"begin\": 3119, \"end\": 3131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Toulson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lois Toulson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Toulson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Toulson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They became the first British divers ever to win a World Championship medal in a women's event with silver last summer, before Yasmin Harper and Scarlett Mew Jensen matched their efforts in the 3m springboard.\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3175, \"end\": 3182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.8113459744317659, \"rank\": 0.14387833553168392, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 3298, \"end\": 3317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scarlett Mew Jensen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spendolini-Sirieix, who was just 16 in Tokyo, said: \\\"With every experience, I have grown as a diver, as a woman, as a human being.\", \"from\": 3364, \"to\": 3494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3403, \"end\": 3408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7829467599616518, \"rank\": 0.27722605076130374, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To have these opportunities is so incredible, I feel so blessed to be able to compete for my country and my home nation and my club.\", \"from\": 3496, \"to\": 3629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think I have anything to prove, I feel like the results speak for themselves so it's just about learning and having fun.\\\"\", \"from\": 3631, \"to\": 3762, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aldi are proud Official Partners of Team GB & ParalympicsGB, supporting all athletes through to Paris 2024  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3764, \"to\": 4102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3764, \"end\": 3768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aldi\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldi\", \"dbpedia\": 